-coriander-plant-at-home-seeds-cuttings-article-233945%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHerZindagi%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20monsoon%2C%20balconies%20or%20window%20ledges%20work%20well.%20If%20rain%20is%20heavy%2C%20move%20your%20pots%20under%20a%20shelter%20to%20protect%20them%20from%20being%20flooded%20or%20battered%20by%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%20Germination%20and%20early%20growth%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYou%20should%20see%20the%20first%20green%20shoots%20emerging%20in%20seven%20to%2010%20days.%20During%20this%20germination%20period%2C%20keep%20the%20soil%20consistently%20moist%20but%20not%20soaked.%20Avoid%20watering%20from%20height%20or%20using%20strong%20streams%20of%20water%2C%20as%20this%20can%20disturb%20the%20delicate%20seedlings.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnce%20the%20seedlings%20are%20a%20few%20inches%20tall%2C%20usually%20at%20the%20two-%20to%20three-week%20mark%2C%20you%20may%20notice%20them%20growing%20closely%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E6.%20Thinning%20the%20seedlings%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20this%20point%2C%20thinning%20becomes%20important.%20Gently%20remove%20the%20weaker%20seedlings%20by%20cutting%20them%20at%20the%20base%2C%20leaving%20about%20two%20inches%20between%20the%20remaining%20plants.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20allows%20each%20plant%20more%20space%2C%20light%2C%20and%20nutrients%20to%20grow%20strong%20and%20leafy.%20You%20can%20compost%20the%20thinned%20seedlings%20or%20even%20use%20them%20as%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F428592%2Fhow-to-grow-microgreens-at-home-step-by-step-process-expert-tips-sujata-agarwal-healthy-living%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emicrogreens%20in%20salads%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ECaring%20for%20your%20coriander%20plant%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWatering%3C%2F